{"LUG":[{"def":"A projecting piece to which anything, as a rod, is attached, or against which anything, as a wedge or key, bears, or through which a bolt passes, etc.","pos":""},{"def":"The leather loop or ear by which a shaft is held up.","pos":""}],"LUGGAGE":[{"def":"That which is lugged; anything cumbrous and heavy to be carried; especially, a traveler's trunks, baggage, etc.","pos":""}],"LUGGER":[{"def":"A small vessel having two or three masts, and a running bowsprit, and carrying lugsails.","pos":""}],"LUGMARK":[{"def":"A mark cut into the ear of an animal to identify it; an earmark.","pos":""}],"LUGSAIL":[{"def":"A square sail bent upon a yard that hangs obliquely to the mast and is raised or lowered with the sail.","pos":""}],"LUGUBRIOUS":[{"def":"Mournful; indicating sorrow, often ridiculously or feignedly; doleful; woful; pitiable; as, a whining tone and a lugubrious look.","pos":""}],"LUGWORM":[{"def":"A large marine annelid (Arenicola marina) having a row of tufted gills along each side of the back.","pos":""}]}